                         Arterial Operations Toolbox

   Contains information to help Traffic Engineers acquire the tools and
   available software packages to optimize their traffic signals and
   effectively operate their arterials. This is a virtual toolbox,
   pertinent information will continuously be added. Please refer to this
   tool box often.

   VIDEOS AND CD’S
   Arterial Signal Timing Video
   This Video will demonstrate the importance and benefits of maintaining
   optimized and current traffic signal timing plans and investing
   resources in traffic signal systems. The video will contain
   testimonials from those who have made the investment. For copies of
   this video and an accompanying tri fold brochure please contact
   pam.crenshaw@fhwa.dot.gov

   Access Management Video
   For a copy please contact pam.crenshaw@fhwa.dot.gov

   Traffic Control Systems Handbook/Freeway Management
   Handbook/Communications Handbooks - on cd rom.
   For a copy please contact pam.crenshaw@fhwa.dot.gov

   COURSES

   Access Management, Location and Design- NHI Course
   www.nhi.fhwa.dot.gov/133078.html

   Actuated Traffic Signals ITS Standards
   Description: This course will provide focused information on actuated
   traffic signals (termed “actuated traffic signal controllers [ASC’s])
   for transportation professionals who are planning, designing,
   procuring, deploying and operating these ITS field devices.   Course
   Length: One day.  Course Sponsor: Institute of Transportation
   Engineers.

   Cost: Free
   To Access This Resource: Contact James Cheeks of the Institute of
   Transportation Engineers,
   (202) 289-0222, ext. 131, JCheeks@ite.org

   Computerized Traffic Signal Systems- NHI Course (available 2001)
   www.nhi.fhwa.dot.gov/133010.html

   Traffic Control Software and Signalization (NHI course# 133028,
   formerly NHI course# 13328)
   www.nhi.fhwa.dot.gov/133028.html

