   What Have We Learned About Intelligent Transportation Systems?
   Chapter 3: Arterial Management (2000)

   This document is an excerpt from a compendium report that looks back on
   the ten years of the National ITS Program to examine which ITS
   technology applications have been successful, which have not been
   successful, and what are the underlying factors that determine success
   versus failure.  This particular section examines arterial management
   systems, such as adaptive traffic signal control, traveler information
   about conditions on arterial streets, automated red light running
   enforcement and traffic signal preemption for emergency vehicles.
   www.itsdocs.fhwa.dot.gov/jpodocs/repts_te/@9z01!.pdf
   EDL# 13319.

   SAFETY

   Stop Red Light Running
   The Stop Red Light Running Program was created by the Federal highway
   Administration in 1995 as community-based safety program.
   safety.fhwa.dot.gov/programs/srlr.htm

   AASHTO Strategic Highway Safety Plan
   Highways: Goal 17 Improving the Design and Operation of Highway
   Intersections
   safetyplan.tamu.edu/plan/goal.asp?GID=17

   ITE Transportation Safety Council
   The Transportation Safety Council covers transportation safety
   improvements and issues, including accident reduction, design and
   safety considerations, work zone safety, human factors, pedestrian and
   bicycle safety and safety considerations for older and disabled people.
   www.ite.org

   ITE Traffic Calming Site
   www.ite.org/traffic/index.html

   ITE Roadway Safety Audits
   www.roadwaysafetyaudits.org

   NATIONAL COOPERATIVE HIGHWAY RESEARCH PROGRAM
   Report 457
   Evaluating Intersection Improvements: An Engineering Study Guide

   This guide describes the engineering study process for evaluating the
   operational effectiveness of various intersection improvements. It
   shows how capacity analysis and traffic simulation models can be used
   to assess the operational impacts of those improvements.
   An enhanced version of this report is available on the world wide web
   at
   http://trb.org/trb/publications/nchrp/esg.pdf
   To order a hardcopy through the Transportation Research Board
   http://www.national-academies.org/trb/bookstore

   INSURANCE INSTITUTE FOR HIGHWAY SAFETY
   STATUS REPORTS
   http://www.highwaysafety.org/pubs.htm

   TRAFFIC SAFETY DIGEST
   A National Highway Traffic Safety Administration quarterly publication
   of innovative state and community traffic safety projects.
   http://www.nhtsa.dot.gov/people/outreach/safedige/

